{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17633502","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17633502"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:55:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:55:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17484"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17484","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17484"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10174"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70719"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10174","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10174"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17484"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56185"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5383"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23777"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23780"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70719","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70719"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA general practitioner is invited to participate in influenza surveillance by submitting weekly reports about influenza-like illness presentations to their practice. This is part of a national surveillance system that includes GP practices across Australia.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes this type of disease surveillance?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Monitoring selected representative sites to track specific conditions","Testing every patient who presents with respiratory symptoms","Random sampling of households in the community","Mandatory reporting of all infectious diseases","Surveying the entire population annually for influenza"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMonitoring selected representative sites\u003C/strong\u003E accurately describes sentinel surveillance, where specific healthcare facilities or providers are chosen to act as monitoring points for particular health conditions. These sentinel sites provide regular, systematic data that can be used to estimate trends in the broader population.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETesting every patient who presents with respiratory symptoms\u003C/strong\u003E describes universal screening which would be unnecessarily resource-intensive and impractical for ongoing surveillance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERandom sampling of households in the community\u003C/strong\u003E describes a cross-sectional survey methodology rather than an ongoing surveillance system.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMandatory reporting of all infectious diseases\u003C/strong\u003E describes notifiable disease surveillance which is a separate system requiring reporting of specific conditions by law.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESurveying the entire population annually for influenza\u003C/strong\u003E describes a census approach which would be too resource-intensive and impractical for regular disease monitoring.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESentinel surveillance is particularly useful for conditions where complete population surveillance would be impractical or unnecessary. The carefully selected sentinel sites must be representative of the population being monitored to provide valid estimates of disease trends.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Sentinel surveillance involves monitoring selected healthcare providers or facilities to track specific diseases or health events.","Sentinel surveillance is useful when complete population surveillance is impractical or resource-intensive.","Sentinel sites are chosen to be representative of the broader population being monitored."],"references":["Cie\u015blak K, Kowalczyk D, Szyma\u0144ski K, Brydak LB. The Sentinel System as the Main Influenza Surveillance Tool. Adv Exp Med Biol. 2017;980:37-43. doi:10.1007/5584_2016_205","Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56185"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17484"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56185","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56185"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:32:01+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T13:32:31+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10174"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70719"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0